<item>
            <title>[LU-15217] disable PCC for encrypted files</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15217</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When files are encrypted in Lustre using fscrypt, they should normally not be accessible to users without the proper encryption key. However, if a user has the encryption key loaded when they read a file, it may be decrypted in memory and saved to the PCC device in unencrypted form.&lt;br/&gt;
For now we should just disable PCC caching of encrypted files.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
